txt.en: Talk to Dardreg at the lumber camp

'If you'd like to make some coin, why not help me? A group of Corsairs passed through Fleetmire recently, south-west of here. They procured more wood than they could carry, so they simply left the logs behind to rot.\n\n'Bring those logs back to me, and I'll consider the job done!'
The Corsairs have left behind some perfectly fine logs, and Dardreg refuses to see them go to waste.

'The bog-lurkers were no match for you, eh? I suppose I ought to start learning a thing or two about dealing with them... or those Corsairs! Ah, but first... Govach must be worried sick, waiting for me.\n\n'I'll be on my way, then. Thanks, [placeholder]!'
You have gathered a good amount of logs.\n\nYou should bring them back to Dardreg, who waits for you at the lumber camp.
Dardreg has asked you to collect freshly-cut logs left behind by Corsairs.\n\nThese logs can be found scattered around Fleetmire, south-west of the lumber camp.
